      <title>Ice Breaker Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/ice-breaker-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/ice-breaker-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 20 Nov 2009 14:01:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Group Party Games]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[ice breaker games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=22</guid>
      <description>Anyone who&amp;#8217;s been to a party before (!) knows the importance of having some ice breaker games at the start to get everyone introduced and into the party spirit. Give everyone sticky name badges so their names and readily visible and get everyone to sit in a circle. Starting with one person, they must describe [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/ice-breaker-games/"&gt;Ice Breaker Games&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com"&gt;Party Games For Girls&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/party-games-for-girls/Party_Games_For_Girls-Ice_Breaker_Games.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Anyone who&#8217;s been to a party before (!) knows the importance of having some ice breaker games at the start to get everyone introduced and into the party spirit.</p>
<p><a title="The Venetian Dream - il gelato" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/26121794@N07/3994756267/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" title="ice breaker games" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2525/3994756267_638bfb6c4c_m.jpg" border="0" alt="The Venetian Dream - il gelato" width="144" height="240" /></a>Give everyone sticky name badges so their names and readily visible and get everyone to sit in a circle. Starting with one person, they must describe their favorite type of ice-cream, but without giving away the flavor. Each other player has to ask &#8216;yes&#8217; and &#8216;no&#8217; questions to discover the flavor.</p>
<p>The party game gets more difficult towards the end as no flavors can be repeated, so the later players have to be more imaginative!</p>
<p><small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="josh.liba" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/26121794@N07/3994756267/" target="_blank">josh.liba</a></small></p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/ice-breaker-games/">Ice Breaker Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
