      <description>If your little girl loves pretending to be a princess, why not make all her dreams come true and hold a princess themed birthday party for her? To do this, make sure that all of her friends come in fancydress. In the past, to focus the guests&amp;#8217; attention on the birthday girl, I have asked [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-party-game-ideas/"&gt;Princess Party Game Ideas&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com"&gt;Party Games For Girls&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/party-games-for-girls/Party_Games_For_Girls-Princess_Party_Game_Ideas.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>If your little girl loves pretending to be a princess, why not make all her dreams come true and hold a princess themed birthday party for her?</p>
<p>To do this, make sure that all of her friends come in fancydress. In the past, to focus the guests&#8217; attention on the birthday girl, I have asked people to come as characters other than princesses; this way, the birthday girl stands out.<span style="float:left;"><a title="Cloud and rainbow" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/29031004@N06/3969102698/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none;" title="princess party game ideas" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2551/3969102698_79f5c2a21b_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Cloud and rainbow" width="144" height="144" /></a></span></p>
<p><span style="float:left;"><a title="Cloud and rainbow" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/29031004@N06/3969102698/" target="_blank"></a></span>To complete the party, you will need to have plenty of princess party game ideas to keep the guests entertained.</p>
<p>How about Princess&#8217; Lost Slipper? Basically a scavenger hunt where you hide one of your daughter&#8217;s shoes and people complete tasks to be given clues as to the whereabouts. Whomever figures out where the slipper is wins!</p>
<p><span style="float: left;"><small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Northampton Museum" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/29031004@N06/3969102698/" target="_blank">Northampton Museum</a></small></span></p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-party-game-ideas/">Princess Party Game Ideas</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
