      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>With Thanksgiving fast approaching, it&#8217;s a great idea to up the ante and give your children some fun outdoor Thanksgiving games to entertain them.<br />
Obviously, the weather is becoming a little less predictable at this time of year, so be prepared to have some blankets on hold! With this in mind, encourage your children to get some fresh air and run about.<br />
<span style="float:left;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/8211018@N03/2866552400/" title="Turkey" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3261/2866552400_71bb7875b7_m.jpg" alt="Turkey" border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/8211018@N03/2866552400/" title="David Reece" target="_blank">David Reece</a></small></span>You could play Turkey Tag, where one person is the tagger (the Farmer) who has to chase and try and catch the others. The children running away are turkeys, so must obviously not be caught by the Farmer for fear of becoming Thanksgiving dinner!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/outdoor-thanksgiving-games/">Outdoor Thanksgiving Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
