      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>If you&#8217;re after holding a mystery party game, you will need to pull together some ideas for some cool <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/mystery-party-games" target=" " title="mystery party games">mystery party games</a>.<br />
<span style="float:left;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/91255327@N00/3424567565/" title="sherlock holmes" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3389/3424567565_c9288d51ba_m.jpg" alt="sherlock holmes" border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" title="Attribution License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/91255327@N00/3424567565/" title="sashafatcat" target="_blank">sashafatcat</a></small></span>To do this, your best bet is to use mystery party kits. These are pre-organized packs of information which require the minimum amount of input from you for the maximum amount of fun for the children.<br />
There are some mystery party kits available online, or you could use the tips on this site for <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/mystery-party-games" target=" " title="mystery party games">mystery party games</a> to create your own unique game. It really depends on how much time you have available and how creative you want to be.<br />
Good luck!</p>
