      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=36</guid>
      <description>It&amp;#8217;s widely accepted that little girls love pretending to be princesses. If you&amp;#8217;re holding a princess party, and want some ideas for some suitable kids princess party games, then here is a suggestion that everyone will enjoy. The game is called Princess Goes Shopping. Sitting in a circle, all of the girls close their eyes. [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/kids-princess-party-games/"&gt;Kids Princess Party Games&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com"&gt;Party Games For Girls&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/party-games-for-girls/Party_Games_For_Girls-Kids_Princess_Party_Games.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>It&#8217;s widely accepted that little girls love pretending to be princesses. If you&#8217;re holding a princess party, and want some ideas for some suitable kids <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/princess-party-games" target=" " title="princess party games">princess party games</a>, then here is a suggestion that everyone will enjoy.</p>
<p>The game is called Princess Goes Shopping. Sitting in a circle, all of the girls close their eyes. In the middle, you put a sack which contains some sweets and some Disney princess party favors.</p>
<p><a title="And in this parcel..." href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/82103247@N00/3846844872/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2542/3846844872_8c7ed547c6_m.jpg" border="0" alt="And in this parcel..." /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="goforchris" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/82103247@N00/3846844872/" target="_blank">goforchris</a></small></p>
<p>Taking turns, each girl puts one hand into the sack and pulls out a prize (it&#8217;s a good idea to have some Disney princess party favors on standby in case some girls get sweets and no Disney princess party favors!).</p>
<p>On picking out a prize, each girl has to invent a story of why she purchased that particular item. No story can be repeated, and it&#8217;s lots of fun to watch the girls try and conjure up ever-increasingly weird stories!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/kids-princess-party-games/">Kids Princess Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
