    <item>
      <title>Some Indoor Party Games Ideas</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games-ideas/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games-ideas/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 18 Oct 2009 12:52:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Indoor Party Games]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[indoor party games ideas]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=156</guid>
      <description>With the weather deteriorating outside (unless you&amp;#8217;re fortunate to live in warmer climates!), if you&amp;#8217;re planning a girl&amp;#8217;s party, you&amp;#8217;ll need to ensure you have some indoor party games ideas to ensure everyone is entertained. A party is a gathering of people ready to have fun. To ensure a cohesive party, I try to incorporate [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games-ideas/"&gt;Some Indoor Party Games Ideas&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com"&gt;Party Games For Girls&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/party-games-for-girls/Party_Games_For_Girls-Some_Indoor_Party_Games_Ideas.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>With the weather deteriorating outside (unless you&#8217;re fortunate to live in warmer climates!), if you&#8217;re planning a girl&#8217;s party, you&#8217;ll need to ensure you have some <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/indoor-party-games" target=" " title="indoor party games">indoor party games</a> ideas to ensure everyone is entertained.</p>
<p>A party is a gathering of people ready to have fun. To ensure a cohesive party, I try to incorporate some team building games to solidify the group and make sure everyone is involved as much as possible.</p>
<p><span style=float:left;><a title="secret" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/75588354@N00/3725306925/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3535/3725306925_4eb7821844_m.jpg" border="0" alt="secret" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="bandita" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/75588354@N00/3725306925/" target="_blank">bandita</a></small></span>One of my favorite team building games is to play BlindMan Walking. To do this, tie some material around one person&#8217;s eyes and then get the other players to give them directions to navigate the room/house. This increases understanding of issues affecting society, as well as trust in one&#8217;s team members. As such, it&#8217;s one of my favorite team building games. Get the girls to swap places. Maybe have more than one person blindfolded at a time. Mix it up and gets the girls to suggest alternatives.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games-ideas/">Some Indoor Party Games Ideas</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
