      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>A really cute idea, which has become one of my favorite girl birthday party ideas is to use some ladybug party supplies.</p>
<p><a title="ladybug_d1004" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/12617189@N03/3988166750/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2522/3988166750_22bc4ede89_m.jpg" border="0" alt="ladybug_d1004" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Juliet Chase" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/12617189@N03/3988166750/" target="_blank">Juliet Chase</a></small></p>
<p>A while ago, I searched online for some ideas for my daughter, and was really inspired by the wide selection of ladybug party supplies I found. You can Google them to see where they&#8217;re sold.</p>
<p>So, basing your party on the ladybug theme will point you in the right direction for when you decide what party games to play. The best thing about this is that you should use the ladybug party supplies that you&#8217;ve bought as inspiration for the games you then play. For example, you could have some facepaint (suitable for children) and paint the girls&#8217; faces to match the pictures on the plates. Another idea would be to play ladybug tag.</p>
<p>Use your imagination and have an awesome time!</p>
