      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Princess tea party games are lots of fun, and let the girls pretend to be princesses while holding a rather civilised tea!</p>
<p>A great one for parents to get their girls to play is the Civilised Princess Game. It&#8217;s played during meal time and each girl has to pretend to eat like a princess would. This is a great way to ensure mealtime is as civilised as possible.</p>
<p><a title="My lemon spice tea" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24532534@N02/3974478204/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2501/3974478204_ffd263323d_m.jpg" border="0" alt="My lemon spice tea" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="moonlightbulb" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24532534@N02/3974478204/" target="_blank">moonlightbulb</a></small></p>
<p>If the girls are a bit older, you could assign each one a country, and the girls have to pretend to be princesses from around the world! This really fires their imaginations!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-tea-party-games/">Princess Tea Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
