      <description>Children love mystery and surprises. As such, it&amp;#8217;s a great idea to include some mystery party games for children at the next party you throw your children. I Spy is a classic game, which can be adapted to become a really involving and fun game. photo credit: Phil Romans To play, one child has to [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-children/"&gt;Mystery Party Games For Children&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com"&gt;Party Games For Girls&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/party-games-for-girls/Party_Games_For_Girls-Mystery_Party_Games_For_Children.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Children love mystery and surprises. As such, it&#8217;s a great idea to include some <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/mystery-party-games" target=" " title="mystery party games">mystery party games</a> for children at the next party you throw your children.</p>
<p>I Spy is a classic game, which can be adapted to become a really involving and fun game.</p>
<p><a title="Baby's eye" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/51035760029@N01/3939665158/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2477/3939665158_5a5b737b10_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Baby's eye" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Phil Romans" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/51035760029@N01/3939665158/" target="_blank">Phil Romans</a></small></p>
<p>To play, one child has to find something in the room or garden. Each player has to guess what the child has chosen but, instead of using words, they have to act out what they think the first child has chosen. It&#8217;s therefore a game where everyone plays throughout, rather than one where each person has a go.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-children/">Mystery Party Games For Children</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
