      <description>When my girls were younger and had birthday parties, it was essential that the games we played were appropriate for the age group. Therefore, when they were at preschool, we played a lot of preschool party games. These tend to be more tame and involve less running around; and they&amp;#8217;re a great opportunity for the [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/preschool-party-games/"&gt;Preschool Party Games&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com"&gt;Party Games For Girls&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/party-games-for-girls/Party_Games_For_Girls-Preschool_Party_Games.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>When my girls were younger and had birthday parties, it was essential that the games we played were appropriate for the age group.</p>
<p>Therefore, when they were at preschool, we played a lot of preschool party games. These tend to be more tame and involve less running around; and they&#8217;re a great opportunity for the children to interact and learn.</p>
<p><a title="En Hemmelighed" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/68978695@N00/3811031103/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3522/3811031103_6d7254a2e7_m.jpg" border="0" alt="En Hemmelighed" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Risager" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/68978695@N00/3811031103/" target="_blank">Risager</a></small></p>
<p>Pass the parcel is a great game for preschoolers. It helps introduce the concept of sharing, and all children love unwrapping presents. Everyone gets a present. However, I&#8217;d make dsure you&#8217;re closeby to ensure little fingers only open only layer of wrapping paper each time!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/preschool-party-games/">Preschool Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
