      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Girls will be girls!</p>
<p>My daughters love playing princess and having princess themed parties. This is a game that you can play with the guests or before the guests arrive (and which will help you organize the rest of the party!).</p>
<p>It&#8217;s generically called &#8216;Princess Decorating Games&#8217;, but basically involves the girls helping to decorate the playzone like a princess&#8217; bedroom or castle.</p>
<p><a title="A Picture of many colors proclaims images of many Thoughts." href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/11767573@N02/3952383451/" target="_blank"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Princess Decorating Games" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3462/3952383451_96d4319bef_m.jpg" border="0" alt="A Picture of many colors proclaims images of many Thoughts." width="240" height="182" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="ManojVasanth" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/11767573@N02/3952383451/" target="_blank">ManojVasanth</a></small></p>
<p>You should supply a variety of colors of crepe papers, tissue paper, ribbons, card, marker pens, glitter and other craft items (including child-safe scissors). You then challenge the girls to create a princess wonderland with placemats, a fortress header for the front door (you should perhaps create the base for this and get the girls to decorate it).</p>
<p>The girls will have a blast and it&#8217;ll make your party venue much more unique than usual!</p>
