      <description><![CDATA[Children love mystery and the unknown. If you can incorporate some mystery party games into your party, the partygoers are sure to have fun. A good example of one of my favorite mystery party games for girls is &#8216;Whose Feet?&#8217;. photo credit: Ken Wilcox. To play this game, you will need some pieces of paper [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-girls/">Mystery Party Games For Girls</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Children love mystery and the unknown. If you can incorporate some <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/mystery-party-games" target=" " title="mystery party games">mystery party games</a> into your party, the partygoers are sure to have fun.</p>
<p>A good example of one of my favorite mystery <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com" target=" " title="party games for girls">party games for girls</a> is &#8216;Whose Feet?&#8217;.</p>
<p><a title="Day 254 - Feet" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/11113739@N04/3911652876/" target="_blank"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Mystery Party Games For Girls" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2469/3911652876_a0ce0cb649_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Day 254 - Feet" width="240" height="160" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Ken Wilcox." href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/11113739@N04/3911652876/" target="_blank">Ken Wilcox.</a></small></p>
<p>To play this game, you will need some pieces of paper and some water-based, child-friendly paint. In turn, each girl will paint the base of her foot, stand on a piece of paper and then wash her foot. The name of each girl will be written on the back of the paper.</p>
<p>Once dried, all of the girls must try and guess whose feet are whose. Be sure to include a print of your feet as well, as this adds a lot of fun because it&#8217;ll create mystery as to who the extra feet belong to!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-girls/">Mystery Party Games For Girls</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-girls/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
