      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>If you&#8217;ve got girls staying over for a slumber party, it&#8217;s a great idea to include some slumber party crafts to keep them entertained. Activities where children get involved are much better than activities where children are passive (e.g. just watching a dvd).</p>
<p>The great thing about slumber parties is that they can be longer than normal parties, so there&#8217;s more choice of which crafts you can include.</p>
<p><a title="disco feva!" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/87457515@N00/3958149550/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2613/3958149550_74d23b46cd_m.jpg" border="0" alt="disco feva!" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Etsy Ketsy" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/87457515@N00/3958149550/" target="_blank">Etsy Ketsy</a></small></p>
<p>Cooking crafts are great for slumber parties, as they&#8217;ll let you bake some cookies or other treats to snack on later. I&#8217;ve also had pillow crafts, where each girl is given a new (freshly washed) pillowcase, some fabric paint and markers, and allowed to decorate the pillowcase that will cover the pillow they will sleep on. This should be done early enough to ensure that the paint dries fully.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-crafts/">Slumber Party Crafts</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-crafts/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Indoor Toddler Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-toddler-party-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-toddler-party-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Sep 2009 08:17:20 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Indoor Party Games]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[indoor toddler party games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=159</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[If you&#8217;re planning a party and there will be some toddlers there (or if your party is for toddlers), you&#8217;ll need to make sure that you include some indoor toddler party games. It&#8217;s best to keep these games as simple as possible, so that the rules can be easily followed. One of my favorites is [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-toddler-party-games/">Indoor Toddler Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>If you&#8217;re planning a party and there will be some toddlers there (or if your party is for toddlers), you&#8217;ll need to make sure that you include some indoor toddler party games.</p>
<p><a title="Elias - Sept 2009" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/19059109@N00/3938692115/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none;" title="Indoor Toddler Party Games" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3527/3938692115_49f41cc84f.jpg" border="0" alt="Elias - Sept 2009" width="350" height="232" /></a></p>
<p>It&#8217;s best to keep these games as simple as possible, so that the rules can be easily followed.</p>
<p>One of my favorites is &#8216;Silent Mice&#8217;. It&#8217;s a bit like &#8216;Musical Statues&#8217;. Play some music and get the children to squeak and jump or roll around like mice. When you stop the music, all of the players must be as quiet and still as possible.</p>
<p>You can either make the loser of each round sit out, or let them join in as a different animal. This keeps them involved.</p>
<p><small><a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" />photo</a> credit: <a title="Shooting Nouns" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/19059109@N00/3938692115/" target="_blank">Shooting Nouns</a></small></p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-toddler-party-games/">Indoor Toddler Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-toddler-party-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>2</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Slumber Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 27 Sep 2009 15:48:27 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Slumber Party Games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=470</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Besides PJs (and maybe teddys!), a slumber party will need slumber party games. With my girls, I prefer incorporating games to DVD after DVD, for two reasons. Firstly, they can watch DVDs any time. Secondly, the interaction and fun they have with games is much higher than by watching a DVD. For this reason, I&#8217;d [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games/">Slumber Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Besides PJs (and maybe teddys!), a slumber party will need <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/slumber-party-games" target=" " title="slumber party games">slumber party games</a>.</p>
<p>With my girls, I prefer incorporating games to DVD after DVD, for two reasons. Firstly, they can watch DVDs any time. Secondly, the interaction and fun they have with games is much higher than by watching a DVD. For this reason, I&#8217;d suggest playing a DVD only towards the end of the night to help them fall asleep.</p>
<p><a title="2007 Sleeping Beauty" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/8563790@N08/1070752417/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1368/1070752417_e1a1d6ef8f_m.jpg" border="0" alt="2007 Sleeping Beauty" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="anoldent" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/8563790@N08/1070752417/" target="_blank">anoldent</a></small></p>
<p>My girls adore play-acting. Therefore, at their slumber parties, each girl is assigned an identity for a portion of the night. If the girls are enjoying it, we then let them choose new identities that everyone has to guess. The person who manages to keep their identity concealed (whilst still acting and talking in their identity, not just by keeping quiet!) wins, and can choose the next game. This ensures all the girls are involved and having fun.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games/">Slumber Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Princess Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-party-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-party-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 26 Sep 2009 15:40:28 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Princess Party Games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=468</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[For some reasons, princess party games always seem to be popular with young girls(!). Princess party games allow the girls&#8217; imaginations to run wild. Whether the theme is a princess party, or whether everyone comes as themselves, games which challenge girls to use their creative side always end up being the games most enjoyed by [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-party-games/">Princess Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>For some reasons, <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/princess-party-games" target=" " title="princess party games">princess party games</a> always seem to be popular with young girls(!).</p>
<p><a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/princess-party-games" target=" " title="Princess party games">Princess party games</a> allow the girls&#8217; imaginations to run wild. Whether the theme is a princess party, or whether everyone comes as themselves, games which challenge girls to use their creative side always end up being the games most enjoyed by the partygoers.</p>
<p><a title="Gizzi and Beth" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/34374129@N00/3826210561/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3426/3826210561_7f707c1ab9_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Gizzi and Beth" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Stuart Chalmers" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/34374129@N00/3826210561/" target="_blank">Stuart Chalmers</a></small></p>
<p>On of our favorites is the Reverse Princess game. In this, prizes are given to those girls who are most un-princesslike (i.e. how they are dressed, their posture, their accents, their behavior). The Princess game follows this, where the girls do the opposite.</p>
<p>Not only is it really fun for the girls to see the difference in their friends, it also allows them to appreciate how their behavior and actions impact on others.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-party-games/">Princess Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
