      <title>Mystery Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-2/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-2/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 25 Sep 2009 15:30:51 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Mystery Party Games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=465</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Mystery party games need not involve anything to do with m*u*r*d*e*r(!). Obviously, they can; it&#8217;s up to you, but this will depend on the age of the girl whose party you&#8217;re planning. The mystery could revolve around who ted-napped the teddy or where the group will be going on a trip or where the birthday [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-2/">Mystery Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p><a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/mystery-party-games" target=" " title="Mystery party games">Mystery party games</a> need not involve anything to do with m*u*r*d*e*r(!). Obviously, they can; it&#8217;s up to you, but this will depend on the age of the girl whose party you&#8217;re planning.</p>
<p>The mystery could revolve around who ted-napped the teddy or where the group will be going on a trip or where the birthday cake is.</p>
<p><a title="a bear checking his flower" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/83997050@N00/3863076959/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3490/3863076959_a8f322cc16_m.jpg" border="0" alt="a bear checking his flower" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="torisan3500" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/83997050@N00/3863076959/" target="_blank">torisan3500</a></small></p>
<p>You could give the partygoers instructions before they arrive at the party as to what the mystery is and what they have to figure out. Maybe everyone has a piece of the clue, and everyone else has to get as many of these as possible. Perhaps the girls are only allowed to ask each other questions in a specified character or do so avoiding a particular word (or words beginning with a particular letter).</p>
<p>The options are pretty endless. I&#8217;ve found it really entertaining to have my girls figure out what they would like the mystery to be. This makes the party really unique and means they&#8217;ll remember it for years to come.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-2/">Mystery Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/mystery-party-games/mystery-party-games-2/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Birthday Party Activities</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/birthday-party-activities/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/birthday-party-activities/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 24 Sep 2009 15:30:08 +0000</pubDate>
