      <category><![CDATA[Birthday Party Activities]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=462</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[One of the key birthday party activities is to have plenty of party games. This site is crammed full of ideas for party games for girls; but not all of our suggestions involve games. Lots of our suggestions involve craft activities too. An excellent way to ensure the party you&#8217;re planning is different from the [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/birthday-party-activities/">Birthday Party Activities</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>One of the key <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/birthday-party-activities" target=" " title="birthday party activities">birthday party activities</a> is to have plenty of party games.</p>
<p>This site is crammed full of ideas for <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com" target=" " title="party games for girls">party games for girls</a>; but not all of our suggestions involve games. Lots of our suggestions involve craft activities too.</p>
<p>An excellent way to ensure the party you&#8217;re planning is different from the (many!) others your guests will go to is to involve some crafts and activities. These can range from baking and dressing up teddy bears to painting pictures, decorating a wall in your garage or decorating a tree in your yard.</p>
<p><a title="City Market Muffins" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/37862156@N00/3927122508/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2445/3927122508_4732254f5a_m.jpg" border="0" alt="City Market Muffins" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="hozae" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/37862156@N00/3927122508/" target="_blank">hozae</a></small></p>
<p>If your party has a theme, the crafts and activities can be centred around it. You could even have a playdate set in advance that all the guests can come to where they make their own costumes that they&#8217;ll wear to the party the following week. You can ask the other moms to supply their daughter with the necessary materials, or you could go through your closet and find clothing you never wear.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s all about engaging the children&#8217;s interests and inspiring them.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/birthday-party-activities/">Birthday Party Activities</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/birthday-party-activities/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Group Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/group-party-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/group-party-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 23 Sep 2009 15:04:42 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Group Party Games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=458</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[A party or playdate would not be complete without some entertaining group party games. These allow the partygoers to engage with each other and develop social skills. When considering what group party games to include, you should bear in mind the following: if you&#8217;re including sporty games, some children might not be so good at [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/group-party-games/">Group Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>A party or playdate would not be complete without some entertaining <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/group-party-games" target=" " title="group party games">group party games</a>.</p>
<p>These allow the partygoers to engage with each other and develop social skills.</p>
<p>When considering what <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/group-party-games" target=" " title="group party games">group party games</a> to include, you should bear in mind the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>if you&#8217;re including sporty games, some children might not be so good at sports, so you should try and think of ways that everyone can feel involved and able to win (maybe as part of a team where their special skill is needed by the whole team)</li>
<li>early exclusion games (whereby someone loses towards the beginning of the game and has to sit out) should not make up the majority of the games &#8211; it&#8217;s better to have a high turnover of games so that everyone can be involved as much as possible</li>
<li>the games that will be enjoyed most are those that the children have helped contribute to, so think of ways they can contribute to the running or judging of the game (whether by choosing rules or catching cheaters, etc)</li>
</ul>
<p><a title="Bad shopping day" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/36514345@N00/3518555635/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3337/3518555635_0ab185afa0_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Bad shopping day" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="wstryder" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/36514345@N00/3518555635/" target="_blank">wstryder</a></small></p>
<p>One of our favorite group party games is The Shopping List game where everyone adds something to the shopping list and it is repeated by everyone in the circle. This can be made more fun by allowing the children to add an action or sing part of the shopping list. Best of all: let the children determine how the rules should be changed!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/group-party-games/">Group Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/group-party-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Outdoor Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/outdoor-party-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/outdoor-party-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 22 Sep 2009 15:04:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Outdoor Party Games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=454</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Regardless of what the weather is like outside, outdoor party games are enjoyed by all children: it&#8217;s just a case of involving them. Allowing the partygoers to play outside in your yard (or a park, properly supervised), will give you some time to organize things inside. It also means that when the children return inside, [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/outdoor-party-games/">Outdoor Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Regardless of what the weather is like outside, <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/outdoor-party-games" target=" " title="outdoor party games">outdoor party games</a> are enjoyed by all children: it&#8217;s just a case of involving them.</p>
<p>Allowing the partygoers to play outside in your yard (or a park, properly supervised), will give you some time to organize things inside. It also means that when the children return inside, they&#8217;ll be a bit more tired and less likely to run around inside too! Not only that, but it will get them to enjoy some physical exercise.</p>
<p>Choosing which games to play should be easy. You could ask the partygoers what they want to play, or you could use the following idea as a start.</p>
<p><a title="DSC_0254" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/7484274@N06/3882206561/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2456/3882206561_3aef41f5ef_m.jpg" border="0" alt="DSC_0254" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="zilupe" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/7484274@N06/3882206561/" target="_blank">zilupe</a></small></p>
<p>Stuck In The Mud is a great way to get everyone running around and enjoying themselves. Basically, one person is the Tagger at the start, and must try and tag everyone else in the group. If the Tagger touches another person, that person is &#8216;stuck&#8217; until another free person runs under their arm or between their legs to free them. If the Tagger gets everyone, she wins.</p>
<p>An interesting alternate version is where, if someone has been &#8216;stuck&#8217; three times, on the fourth time, they also become a Tagger.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/outdoor-party-games/">Outdoor Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/outdoor-party-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Indoor Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 21 Sep 2009 14:45:08 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Indoor Party Games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=442</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[When planning a girl&#8217;s party, you have the choice of whether you want to play the party games inside or outside. Deciding whether to include some indoor party games into the party you are planning will depend on several factors, including the chosen theme, the desires of the partygirl and the weather. Just because the [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games/">Indoor Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>When planning a girl&#8217;s party, you have the choice of whether you want to play the party games inside or outside.</p>
<p>Deciding whether to include some <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/indoor-party-games" target=" " title="indoor party games">indoor party games</a> into the party you are planning will depend on several factors, including the chosen theme, the desires of the partygirl and the weather.</p>
<p><a title="fast" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/7941044@N06/2682800311/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3008/2682800311_0711f6564d_m.jpg" border="0" alt="fast" width="160" height="240" /></a></p>
<p>Just because the party games are to be played inside doesn&#8217;t mean they have to be subdued and boring games. Games such as musical chairs, musical statues and hide and seek can all be played inside. Any game which is ordinarily played outside can have its rules altered to allow it to be played inside.</p>
<p>Take a game such as &#8216;tag&#8217;. Usually, this should be played outside, but if the rules of the game require the children to speak and pursue in slow motion, it can be played inside. Anyone breaching the rules has to sit out.</p>
<p>The best thing about adapting games so they are suitable to become <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/indoor-party-games" target=" " title="indoor party games">indoor party games</a>, is that the children can be involved in determining how the rules should change &#8211; this will make them more likely to stick to the rules and also engages them with the party.</p>
<p>Enjoy!</p>
<p><small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="jenny downing" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/7941044@N06/2682800311/" target="_blank">jenny downing</a></small></p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games/">Indoor Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-party-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Slumber Party Games To Play</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games-to-play/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games-to-play/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Sep 2009 14:17:20 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Slumber Party Games]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[slumber party games to play]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=196</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[One of the most fun slumber party games to play is Who Am I. You will need five scraps of paper per girl and a container. Using the scraps of paper, each girl writes down the names of five famous people or other people known to all of the group. The scraps are then folded [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games-to-play/">Slumber Party Games To Play</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>One of the most fun <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/slumber-party-games" target=" " title="slumber party games">slumber party games</a> to play is Who Am I.</p>
<p>You will need five scraps of paper per girl and a container.</p>
<p>Using the scraps of paper, each girl writes down the names of five famous people or other people known to all of the group. The scraps are then folded up and put into the container.</p>
<p><a title="oh what fun" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/14012543@N04/2369710781/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3185/2369710781_b4632d6b24_m.jpg" border="0" alt="oh what fun" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="corresponding shapes" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/14012543@N04/2369710781/" target="_blank">corresponding shapes</a></small></p>
<p>The girls will need to be divided into two groups, with just one girl in each group (at a time) taking a name from the container. This girl will need to give her team members clues as to what name she has, without saying the name. When the other members of her team have guessed the name, the next person in the team takes a name from the container, and so on.</p>
<p>Both teams play at the same time, until all of the names are used. The team which guesses the most names wins.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games-to-play/">Slumber Party Games To Play</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/slumber-party-games-to-play/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>3</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Silly Party Games</title>
      <link>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/silly-party-games/</link>
      <comments>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/silly-party-games/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 19 Sep 2009 14:10:10 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Party Games For Girls</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Group Party Games]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[silly party games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=29</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Parties are all about having fun. Because of this, it&#8217;s always fun to incorporate some silly party games into the list of games you plan to play. One of these is the Emotions Game. photo credit: tiffanywashko To play this game, one person will need to leave the room, while the other girls decide on [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/silly-party-games/">Silly Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Parties are all about having fun. Because of this, it&#8217;s always fun to incorporate some silly party games into the list of games you plan to play.</p>
<p>One of these is the Emotions Game.</p>
<p><a title="Smile" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/33986404@N00/3513706834/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3405/3513706834_7ea3f6be7e_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Smile" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="tiffanywashko" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/33986404@N00/3513706834/" target="_blank">tiffanywashko</a></small></p>
<p>To play this game, one person will need to leave the room, while the other girls decide on an emotion. When the person returns to the room, each of the girls have to pose, sing, dance or act that emotion. The aim of the game is for the person who left the room to guess the emotion.</p>
<p>Each of the girls can take it in turns to be the person leaving the room. Obviously, the more rounds of the game that are played, the harder and more funny it gets!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/silly-party-games/">Silly Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
