      <description><![CDATA[Ok, so not all girls like being princesses. But, even if they do, not all pirates have to be male and wear patches&#8230; A fun party where both girls and boys are coming is to have a pirate theme. For this, you will need some pirate birthday party activities. Maybe the birthday girl is the [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/pirate-birthday-party-activities/">Pirate Birthday Party Activities</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Ok, so not all girls like being princesses. But, even if they do, not all pirates have to be male and wear patches&#8230;</p>
<p>A fun party where both girls <em>and </em>boys are coming is to have a pirate theme. For this, you will need some pirate <a class="ld_link" href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/birthday-party-activities" target=" " title="birthday party activities">birthday party activities</a>.</p>
<p>Maybe the birthday girl is the Captain of the Ship. Obviously, games like treasure hunt and &#8216;find the ticking clock before the alarm rings&#8217; are good fun, but one that&#8217;s also fun is Walk The Plank To Safety.</p>
<p><a title="Windy. Aarrrr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/99139484@N00/3572364633/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3587/3572364633_8cdb130933_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Windy. Aarrrr" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="kevygee" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/99139484@N00/3572364633/" target="_blank">kevygee</a></small></p>
<p>For this game, draw a plank on the ground with chalk and blindfold each child in turn. The aim is for the child to walk in a straight line and reach the other side without &#8216;falling off&#8217;. Along each side of the plank, the other children can stand with squirt bottles, pretending to be crocodiles. If the plank-walker &#8216;falls off&#8217; the plank, the other children can squirt them.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/pirate-birthday-party-activities/">Pirate Birthday Party Activities</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/pirate-birthday-party-activities/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
