      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>This is one of the funniest indoor icebreaker games we&#8217;ve come across.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s one we made up (and have tested over and over again!) called Princess Witch Diva.</p>
<p><a title="Caireles sonriente" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/10459444@N06/1042286886/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1384/1042286886_b76aa17e16_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Caireles sonriente" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="~*Bomba Rosa*~" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/10459444@N06/1042286886/" target="_blank">~*Bomba Rosa*~</a></small></p>
<p>This game is a lot like scissors/papers/stones, but it&#8217;s a lot more dramatic and a great way for a new group of girls to relax around each other.</p>
<p>On the count of three (or when suitable music is stopped), all of the girls pose as a princess, a witch or a diva. The Princess beats the Witch, the Witch beats the Diva and the Diva beats the Princess. Keep going until all the girls are out!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/indoor-icebreaker-games/">Indoor Icebreaker Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
