      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Traditionally, outdoor youth games are for youth groups and are designed to cater for larger groups of children. A game which involves everyone is a fun way of uniting the group.</p>
<p>One game is RED ROVER RED ROVER. To play this, the group will need to be divided into equal (or near equal) groups.</p>
<p>Each group stands in a line and takes turns in shouting &#8220;red rover red rover&#8221;. The first person in the line of the shouting group then names someone on the other team. As soon as that person&#8217;s name is shouted, they have to run towards the shouting group and try and break through their line.</p>
<p>The other side does the same, and each side takes turns, working along the line so everyone gets a chance to shout someone&#8217;s name. Whichever side gets all their team through wins.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s a great way to learn people&#8217;s names and to get everyone ready for some quieter games later!</p>
<p><a title="Fast as fast can be!" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/30055326@N05/3813323041/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2669/3813323041_ac933d7171_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Fast as fast can be!" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absMiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="jenny818" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/30055326@N05/3813323041/" target="_blank">jenny818</a></small></p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/outdoor-youth-games/">Outdoor Youth Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
