      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Sometimes it&#8217;s good for party games to be played outside. This idea will provide you with some really fun games for kids outside.</p>
<p><a title="IXS_7123" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/35034350386@N01/3745963402/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2485/3745963402_4729331c12_m.jpg" border="0" alt="IXS_7123" /></a>You&#8217;ll need some chalk and some outside space. On the ground, use the chalk to mark out a grid measuring at least four square by four squares. Each square should be large enough for a girl to stand in.</p>
<p>Then use dice (or a large box painted like a dice) to roll numbers. Each girl will roll the dice individually and will move the corresponding number of spaces. Each sqaure will have a task or an action which the landing girl will have to perform &#8211; these can be decided by you in advance, or the girls could put their ideas into a hat for you to reveal when each girl rolls the dice! Lots of fun!</p>
