      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Three great ways play a fun princess dress up game are to have the girls trying to look like (a) the best princess ever, (b) the worst princess ever or (c) a combination of both.</p>
<p><a title="Two Real Princesses" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/10485077@N06/3283786500/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3225/3283786500_e169ef143b_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Two Real Princesses" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="edenpictures" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/10485077@N06/3283786500/" target="_blank">edenpictures</a></small></p>
<p>It would be a great idea to have a few bags of clothes or fabric samples so the girls can put together their own outfits, along with some hair clips, hair ties and glitter make-up. A way to inject fun is to give the girls five minutes to put their best princess &#8216;look&#8217; together; and then to give them two minutes to get them to put their worst princess &#8216;look&#8217; together.</p>
<p>Sometimes it&#8217;s fun to not tell them about the second task; be sure to have a video camera closeby for their responses!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/princess-party-games/princess-dress-up/">Princess Dress Up</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
