      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>A theme that is always popular with girls is to have a tea birthday party.</p>
<p>Although it might seem obvious that tea is needed, this is not so, as a tea birthday party is characterized by having adult-type food and drink in child-friendly (and tasty!) portions. You could even spice it up by having an Alice in Wonderland theme with fancy dress.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/51035626656@N01/2338654569/" title="IMG_0296.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2166/2338654569_41e08d548a_m.jpg" alt="IMG_0296.jpg" border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/51035626656@N01/2338654569/" title="ste3ve" target="_blank">ste3ve</a></small></p>
<p>If the girls coming to your party don&#8217;t like tea, why not make some fruity drinks which make it look they&#8217;re drinking tea? Naturally, these are served from a tea pot. Small sandwiches, cakes, fruit and other treats are also made to accompany the &#8216;tea&#8217;.</p>
<p>These parties are particularly suitable for girly girls, so the party games you hold should bear this in mind.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/tea-birthday-party/">Tea Birthday Party</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/tea-birthday-party/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
