]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>One of the best sleepover party ideas is to let the girls camp overnight in your garden!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/10563005@N06/2609614626/" title="Outdoor play." target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3248/2609614626_92756eb704_m.jpg" alt="Outdoor play." border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" title="Attribution License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/10563005@N06/2609614626/" title="lori05871" target="_blank">lori05871</a></small></p>
<p>Depending on how boisterous the girls are, you can organize hide and seek games, lost and found games, water balloon games, etc. It&#8217;s also a great chance to have the girls get involved in cooking some healthy and brightly colored foods (like peppers, crazily-topped pizzas and exotic fruits).</p>
<p>Some ghost stories can be exchanged in the tent before bedtime (obviously age-dependant ones!), and the girls can either stay in the tent(s) or watch a dvd voted on by them all inside. Great memorable fun!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/slumber-party-games/sleepover-party-ideas/">Sleepover Party Ideas</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
