      <category><![CDATA[party word games]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/?p=27</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Girls have lots of fun playing party word games, and here&#8217;s one which is guaranteed to be fun. Divide the girls into two teams and sit them opposite each other in two rows so each girl is facing one other girl. If there are an odd number of girls, the extra girl will sit at [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/party-word-games/">Party Word Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Girls have lots of fun playing party word games, and here&#8217;s one which is guaranteed to be fun.</p>
<p>Divide the girls into two teams and sit them opposite each other in two rows so each girl is facing one other girl. If there are an odd number of girls, the extra girl will sit at the head of the rows.</p>
<p>Each girl must try to get the girl opposite her to say one word from a particular list of words (maybe based on the party&#8217;s theme). Whichever row has the largest number of girls able to make her opponent say one of the words wins!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/27324323@N03/3814382893/" title="love" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2544/3814382893_cb85db9637_m.jpg" alt="love" border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/27324323@N03/3814382893/" title="courtney____" target="_blank">courtney____</a></small></p>
<p>If there&#8217;s an odd number of girls, the remaining girl can choose who to play against after everyone has played. She could therefore change the outcome of which team wins!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/party-word-games/">Party Word Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/party-word-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
