      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Girls really enjoy helping to organize a party. Getting them to help put together birthday party crafts is a great way to make the party unique <em>and</em> give you time to focus on other aspects of the party.</p>
<p>The crafts can be table decorations, name badges, pictures to decorate a room, party bag covers; the list is endless!</p>
<p>Essential supplies would be plenty of colored paper, non-toxic glue, appropriate scissors and lots of glitter! It&#8217;s also a good idea to have some sparkly paper which the girls can cut to make shapes or letters.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/33986404@N00/3611844394/" title="Beading" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2452/3611844394_55502a58dc_m.jpg" alt="Beading" border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" title="Attribution License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/33986404@N00/3611844394/" title="tiffanywashko" target="_blank">tiffanywashko</a></small></p>
<p>You&#8217;ll probably want to provide aprons for the girls and coverings for the tables/floors where the crafts are being made.</p>
<p>Be sure to include some time for the actual party though!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/birthday-party-activities/birthday-party-crafts/">Birthday Party Crafts</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
