      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Pool party games can be enjoyed by all sorts of girls. One excellent game to play is to have a mermaid swimming competition. You&#8217;ll need at least two girls (mermaids) and an appropriate number of adult supervisors.</p>
<p><a title="Give me a break...in the pool" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/62424894@N00/183286968/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/74/183286968_c1d09a455b_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Give me a break...in the pool" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Tom@HK" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/62424894@N00/183286968/" target="_blank">Tom@HK</a></small></p>
<p>Each girl will be given the chance to swim as much like a mermaid as possible. However, it&#8217;s up to each mermaid to decide the character of their mermaid and to get into character!</p>
<p>The contest can be judged by the adult supervisors or by all the mermaids collectively. This is probably the best option because all girls get to participate in deciding who wins. Let the best Mermaid win!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/pool-party-games/">Pool Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/pool-party-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
