      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Come rain or shine, a picnic party is great fun. A key ingredient to their success is incorporating cool picnic party games to keep the girls entertained.</p>
<p>The sorts of games that can be played will depend on whether your picnic party is being held indoors or outdoors. Girls whose birthdays are in the fall or winter sometimes miss out on being able to have their own picnic party; this need not be the case (and will definitely be a party everyone will remember!).</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/20119917@N04/3848327720/" title="" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3435/3848327720_551b076699_m.jpg" alt="" border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/20119917@N04/3848327720/" title="m,!" target="_blank">m,!</a></small></p>
<p>A great idea is to hide some prizes at various places around the house (or garden) and to give the girls clues to find the prizes. The clues and prizes can match the sort of picnic you are throwing, whether it be a traditional teddy bear&#8217;s picnic or a fairy twinkle toes picnic with tag games and sticky chicken wings! Let your imagination go wild!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/picnic-party-games/">Picnic Party Games</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/outdoor-party-games/picnic-party-games/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
