      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>A great way to break the ice at a party is to have a kids&#8217; dance party. This can be done either with or without boys, and sometimes the most fun dance parties are those where the girls rule. Alone!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/74058182@N00/3588519028/" title="wedding meetup10" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2483/3588519028_e073c7fb59_m.jpg" alt="wedding meetup10" border="0" /></a><br /><small><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" alt="Creative Commons License" border="0" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/74058182@N00/3588519028/" title="ex animø" target="_blank">ex animø</a></small></p>
<p>There are many ways a dance party can be organized, on every kind of budget. There could be a theme (like High School Musical or fairy garden princesses!) that the girls choose beforehand. The theme would give the girls a chance to start enjoying the party before it happens (and makes it much easier to keep them entertained!). Or the party could be themeless, with some fun songs chosen by the girls (and played by a DJ &#8211; or mom and dad!).</p>
<p>Let the dancing begin!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/indoor-party-games/kids-dance-party-2/">Kids Dance Party</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
