      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>Girls and boys tend to like playing different types of games at parties. When you&#8217;re planning a party and you know there&#8217;ll be a mix of boys and girls, a treasure hunt game is a great way to get everyone involved and having fun.</p>
<p>A fairly easy and inexpensive way to ensure each stop on the treasure hunt is suitable for everyone is to have candy as the treasure.</p>
<p><a title="Sabores" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/38804287@N07/3804633122/" target="_blank"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2450/3804633122_32f148e11c_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Sabores" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Fújur" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/38804287@N07/3804633122/" target="_blank">Fújur</a></small></p>
<p>The players can either eat the candy as they go or trade the candy in for a suitable prize at the end. The players who eat fewer candies will benefit the most; perhaps even a great way to combat our growing childhood obesity problems!</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.PartyGamesForGirls.com/group-party-games/treasure-hunt-game/">Treasure Hunt Game</a> is a post from: <a href="http://www.partygamesforgirls.com">Party Games For Girls</a> blog where you can get great ideas for children's party games and the latest news on party games for girls</p>
]]></content:encoded>
